  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my TESCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit TESCO reference number in the bill checker at the top of this page and click Check Bill. Your complete TESCO electricity bill for March 2026 appears in seconds — showing amount due, due date, units consumed, and all charges. This is free, requires no login, and works 24/7 for all tribal district consumers." },
    { question: "What is the difference between TESCO and PESCO?", answer: "TESCO (Tribal Areas Electricity Supply Company) supplies electricity exclusively to the seven Merged Tribal Districts formerly known as FATA: Khyber, Kurram, North Waziristan, South Waziristan, Bajaur, Mohmand, and Orakzai. PESCO (Peshawar Electric Supply Company) covers the settled KPK districts: Peshawar, Mardan, Swat, Abbottabad, Kohat, Bannu, and D.I. Khan. Check your bill heading to confirm which company supplies you." },
    { question: "How do I check my TESCO bill for Parachinar (Kurram)?", answer: "Parachinar and all of Kurram district are within TESCO's service area. Enter your 14-digit TESCO reference number in the bill checker above — the same tool works for Parachinar City, Sadda, Tall, Alizai, and all Kurram district connections. Kurram is one of TESCO's largest districts by consumer count." },
    { question: "How do I check my TESCO bill for Bajaur (Khar)?", answer: "Bajaur district including Khar, Mamund, Nawagai, and Charmang is under TESCO. Enter your 14-digit reference number in the checker above. Bajaur is TESCO's second most populous district and has seen significant electricity network expansion since the 2018 KPK merger." },
    { question: "What are TESCO's winter peak hours?", answer: "TESCO winter peak hours (November to March) are 5:00 PM to 9:00 PM — one full hour earlier than most Pakistani DISCOs. This reflects the earlier winter sunset in KPK's high-altitude mountain terrain. Avoid running washing machines, electric geysers, and irons between 5 PM and 9 PM in winter to save on per-unit charges." },
    { question: "How do I download my TESCO duplicate bill?", answer: "After your bill loads in the checker, click Download PDF. In the browser print dialog, select Save as PDF and click Save. Your TESCO duplicate bill downloads instantly as a PDF — ready to pay at JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank in Peshawar or your district." },
    { question: "How do I pay my TESCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank mobile app. Select Electricity, choose TESCO or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount, and confirm. JazzCash agents are widely available across tribal districts including Khar (Bajaur), Parachinar (Kurram), and Bara (Khyber)." },
    { question: "Why does load shedding last so long in tribal areas?", answer: "TESCO areas experience some of Pakistan's longest load shedding durations due to: (1) Long transmission lines across mountainous terrain with higher technical losses; (2) Historically lower bill recovery rates in some tribal districts; (3) Ongoing grid infrastructure upgrades following the 2018 KPK merger. Urban area consumers in Khar, Parachinar, and Miranshah typically see 6–12 hours; remote rural areas can see more. Regular bill payment directly contributes to improving your feeder's supply allocation." },
    { question: "What is the TESCO grace period for bill payment?", answer: "TESCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After the grace period, a 10% surcharge applies to the unpaid amount. In remote tribal areas where paper bills do not arrive, always check your due date online using this tool before it passes." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with TESCO?", answer: "Call TESCO helpline 118 or 091-9212964 with your reference number. Alternatively, send your complaint by SMS to 8118 with your 14-digit reference number and a brief description. Get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN). TESCO must resolve within 14 working days. Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 if unresolved." },
  ]}

